In order to understand the reproducibilty of ICSC modularization on a subset of the dataset, we divided the HCP dataset into three folds, such that the average age of the subjects and the gender ratio in each fold is maintained. We ran 20 independent runs on the subject data in each fold and selected the run with the maximum consensus-cost. We found that the modularizations obtained from different folds were not only similar to each other (AMI = \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
